'''通往地狱的道路充满了善意'''是一句[[谚语|谚语]]或[[格言|格言]]。另一种形式是“'''地狱充满了美好的意义，而天堂充满了美好的作品'''”。 <ref>{{Citation|title=Proverbs|page=234|publisher=Infobase Publishing|year=2007|isbn=9780816066735|chapter=the road to Hell is paved with good intentions}}</ref>

== 起源 ==
这个谚语的确切起源是未知的，它的形式已经随着时间而演变。现代表达方式“通往[[地狱|地狱]]的道路充满了善意”于1855年首次发表在{{link-en|亨利·博恩|Henry George Bohn}}的《谚语手册》中。<ref>{{Citation|url=https://archive.org/details/ahandbookprover01raygoog/page/n525|title=A Hand-book of Proverbs|first=Henry|last=Bohn|year=1855}}</ref> 1670年，[[约翰·雷|约翰·雷]]（[[约翰·雷|John Ray]]）收集了《英语谚语集》（A Collection of English Proverbs），其中出版了一个更早的版本《地狱充满了美好的寓意和愿望》。 <ref>{{Citation|url=https://archive.org/details/acompleatcollec00raygoog/page/n33|title=A Collection of English Proverbs|first=John|last=Ray|year=1670}}</ref> 最早的类似此短语的文字出现在[[维吉尔|维吉尔]]（Virgil）的[[埃涅阿斯纪|Aeneid]]中：“facilis descensus Averno（下降到地狱很容易）”。<ref>{{Citation|title=Analogous Proverbs In Ten Languages|chapter=Hell is paved with good intentions|first=Mrs E. B.|last=Mawr|year=1885|publisher=Elliot Stock}}</ref> 

圣经中的相似语句可以在[[便西拉智訓|便西拉智訓]] 21:10找到，“The way of sinners is made plain with stones, but at the end thereof is the pit of hell.”<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.bible.com/bible/546/SIR.21.10.KJVA|title=King James Bible}}</ref> 谚语一般错误被认为是[[伯爾納鐸|伯爾納鐸]]写的（约1150年），“L'enfer est plein de bonnes volontés ou désirs”（地狱充满了美好的愿望或欲望）。<ref>{{Citation|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9re1vfFh04sC&pg=PA542|title=The American Heritage dictionary of idioms|first=Christine|last=Ammer|isbn=9780395727744|year=1997|accessdate=2020-09-15|archive-date=2020-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200916164849/https://books.google.com/books?id=9re1vfFh04sC&pg=PA542|dead-url=no}}</ref>引用是在他去世大约五百年后的1640年发生的，在他的任何出版作品中都没有发现该文本。

[[穆罕默德|穆罕默德]]曾在[[聖訓|圣训]]中写过相似的一句话：“天堂被困苦所包围，大火被欲望所包围。”

== 含义 ==
该短语的一个普遍含义是，个人可能有意采取良好的行动，但是却没有采取行动。<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/the+road+to+hell+is+paved+with+good+intentions|title=The road to hell is paved with good intentions|publisher=Dictionary.com/[[Houghton_Mifflin_Company|Houghton Mifflin Company]]|work=The American Heritage New Dictionary of Cultural Literacy|edition=Third|year=2005|accessdate=March 28, 2013|archive-date=2015-09-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150909230205/http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/the+road+to+hell+is+paved+with+good+intentions|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite book|url=http://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/british/the-road-to-hell-is-paved-with-good-intentions|title=The road to hell is paved with good intentions|publisher=Dictionary.cambridge.org/[[Cambridge_University_Press|Cambridge University Press]]|work=Cambridge Advanced Learner's Dictionary & Thesaurus|edition=Third|year=2008|accessdate=March 28, 2013|archive-date=2015-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722045555/http://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/british/the-road-to-hell-is-paved-with-good-intentions|dead-url=no}}</ref>这种无所作为可能是由于[[延宕|拖延]]，[[懶惰|懒惰]]或其他的恶习。<ref>{{Citation|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PGiREb_p238C&pg=PA33|title=101 American English proverbs: understanding language and culture through commonly used sayings|first=Harry|last=Collis|first2=Mario|last2=Risso|chapter=The Road to Hell is Paved with Good Intentions|isbn=9780844254128|year=1992|place=Lincolnwood, Ill|publisher=Passport Books|url=https://archive.org/details/101americanengli00harr_0}}</ref>因此，这句话是一个警告，表示良好的意图如果不遵循是没有意义的。<ref>{{Cite book|title=Psychosocial Basis of Health Care|url=https://archive.org/details/psychosocialbasi0000unse|first=Charles L., editor|last=Bowden|first2=Alvin George, editor|last2=Burstein|page=[https://archive.org/details/psychosocialbasi0000unse/page/98 98]|publisher=Williams & Wilkins|year=1983|isbn=0-683-00993-1}}</ref>

这种说法的另一种解释是，经常有人[[善意|善意]]地做错事或[[恶行|恶行]]。或是好意可能会带来{{le|意想不到的后果|Unintended consequences}}。一个例子是引入[[入侵物种|入侵物种]]，例如在[[美国|美国]]引入[[亞洲鯉魚|亚洲鲤鱼]]。<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/resilience-bullying/201008/principle-one-road-hell-is-paved-good-intentions|journal=Psychology Today|series=Resilience to Bullying|first=Izzy|last=Kalman|title=Principle Number One: The Road to Hell is Paved with Good Intentions|date=August 16, 2010}}</ref>

亦有理解為：善意且[[無知|無知]]的行為可能導向悲慘的結果。如：錯誤的政策比[[貪污|貪污]]更可怕。

